description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;ODCS Assistant Manager&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;NHS North of England Commissioning Support (NECS) works across the UK to support health and social care customers in meeting their strategic and operational challenges; improving outcomes and increasing efficiency. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our current customers include local authorities, Clinical Commissioning Groups (CCGs), a range of healthcare providers, and third and private sector organisations. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity is now available to be involved in the development, delivery and management of a programme of organisation development work designed to ‘create jobs and generate wealth for our communities’, directly delivering on our social purpose mission.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All aspects of programme and project management will be required including:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create and maintain a project plan, risk log etc. to support effective management of the project&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Produce highlight project reports, ensuring risks and issues are escalated as appropriate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work closely with existing managers and teams to provide specialist advice and support, including on new ways of working, such as how to integrate new colleagues potentially transitioning in to employment for the first time in a virtual world&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create processes, procedures and guidance documents&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create an induction and on-boarding programme for new colleagues&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will include the matrix management of project support colleagues. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the project becomes ready to move to BAU a close down report will be needed to review and assess the success of the project, and identify any actions needed to ensure on-going success. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In order to be successful in this role you will need;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A background in Organisation Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be able to work well under pressure, managing conflicting deadlines and priorities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have excellent stakeholder management skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong project management understanding and experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
